The All Progressive Congress (APC) says the fusion of former president, Olusegun Obasanjo’s Coalition for Nigeria Movement (CNM) into the African Democratic Congress (ADC) was not a threat to president Muhammadu Buhari’s 2019 presidential ambition. In a statement by the National Publicity Secretary of the party, Mallam Bolaji Abdullahi, APC noted that Nigerians still believe in them because of the changes they are bringing on board. APC maintained that Nigeria was in multi-party democracy and the Nigerian people will decide which party they will give their mandate to when the time comes. “We are in a multi-party democracy and the coming together by political parties should not be considered a threat.” he said “In fact, the more the merrier, we do not see this as a threat at all. “We are confident that Nigerians still believe in our party they are seeing the changes we are bringing on board “The Nigerian people will decide which party among the very many they will give their mandate to when the time comes.” he added   Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook